t developed with the backend framework Node.js leveraging the powerful socket.io library, which is a javascript library open source for dual communication between server and client. In the chat room developed it demonstrated its use in three different browsers with three different users. The back end was developed with Node.js and deployed on a free Heroku server account and the frontend was developed with the React framework and deployed on the free Netlify account. As a final note in order to enter in a specific chatting room, the name of the person joining the conversation has to put specifically the name of the room they intend to join for thor discussion as shown in Figure 2 below:"), mdx("p", null, mdx("span", {
